# Tech Stack And Runtime Rules

- Frontend: Next.js 16 App Router with `src/` directory structure.
- DB/Auth/Vector: Supabase (`PostgreSQL + pgvector`) via `@supabase/ssr`.
- AI:
  - LLM: Claude 3.5 Sonnet
  - Embedding: OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small`
- UI: Shadcn UI (Nova preset) + Tailwind CSS.
- Deploy: Vercel.
- Test: Jest (+ ts-jest), with calculator unit tests first.

## Next.js 16 Specifics

- Use `proxy.ts` (not legacy `middleware.ts`) for request guard/session refresh behavior.
- Prefer Server Components; use `"use client"` only when interactive state/event handling is needed.

## Server Action Constraint

- In `"use server"` files, export only `export async function ...`.
- Do not export objects/constants/defaults from server-action-only modules.

## TypeScript

- Keep strict-mode-friendly code.
- Avoid `any`; use explicit interfaces/types and narrow unknown data safely.
